---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="OpenTeams Privacy Policy. How OpenTeams, Inc. collects, uses, shares, and stores your Personal Information when you use our Services."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="OpenTeams"
    title="Privacy Policy"
    lead="Last updated: July 2025"
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          This privacy policy explains how OpenTeams, Inc. (“We,” “Our,” “Us”)
          use Personally Identifiable Information (“Personal Information”)
          collected from You (“User,” “You”) when You use Our website or Our
          online user portal (collectively, the “Services”).
        </p>

        <h2>1. What Information Do We Collect?</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Information You Provide to Us:</strong> We collect Personal
          Information directly from You through forms, content submissions,
          registration processes, customer service interactions, or other user
          engagements with Our Services. This includes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Contact Data:</strong> Full name, address, city, state, zip
            code, phone number, email address, third-party communication handles
            (e.g., Slack, Twitter, Facebook).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Financial Data:</strong> Information required to process
            payments, such as credit card or bank account information.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Voluntarily Provided Information:</strong> Feedback or other
            personal data submitted through optional forms.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>User-Contributed Data:</strong> Profiles, chat logs, and
            networking interactions you voluntarily share, which may be made
            publicly available or shared per Our Terms of Service.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Information Collected Automatically:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Traffic and Log Data:</strong> IP address, browser type,
            ISP, OS, referral pages, page views, visit times, and similar
            metadata.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cookies:</strong> Small data files stored on Your device to
            enhance and personalize the user experience. See our Cookie Notice
            below for more information.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Third-party Data Collection:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Services (Analytics, AdSense, Tag Manager):</strong>{' '}
            Track usage patterns, referrals, and user behaviors.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Meta (Facebook) Pixel:</strong> Measure ad effectiveness and
            retarget users.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>reCAPTCHA v3:</strong> Protect forms from abuse and spam,
            subject to Google’s Privacy Policy.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>RB2B and Retargeting:</strong> When you visit or log in to
            our website, cookies and similar technologies may be used by our
            online data partners or vendors to associate your activity with
            other personal information they or others have about you, including
            your email. We (or service providers on our behalf) may then send
            marketing to these emails.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can opt out at{' '}
          <a href="https://app.retention.com/optout">https://app.retention.com/optout</a>.
          If governed by GDPR, you can also opt out via{' '}
          <a href="https://www.rb2b.com/rb2b-gdpr-opt-out">https://www.rb2b.com/rb2b-gdpr-opt-out</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>2. How Do We Use Your Information?</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To deliver, maintain, and improve Our Services.</li>
          <li>To facilitate transactions and process payments.</li>
          <li>To communicate with You about Our Services and products.</li>
          <li>To respond to inquiries and customer support requests.</li>
          <li>
            To enhance user experience through analytics and personalized
            content.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How Do We Share Information?</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Order Processing:</strong> With third-party payment
            processors.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Affiliates and Service Providers:</strong> To support
            business operations, maintenance, and product improvement.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Marketing:</strong> With select partners or platforms to
            enhance professional networking and targeted outreach. You can opt
            out at any time.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Required by Law:</strong> To comply with legal
            investigations or protect rights and safety.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Change in Control / Bankruptcy:</strong> Personal Information
            may be disclosed as part of a corporate transaction, with
            notification where applicable.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>User-Contributed Data:</strong> Shared publicly or with
            registered users depending on platform features and user consent.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>By Consent:</strong> Any other sharing of data will be with
          Your explicit consent.
        </p>

        <h2>4. How Do We Store Your Information?</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Retention:</strong> Personal Information is kept as long as
            necessary to provide Services or meet legal obligations.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Security:</strong> Reasonable security measures are in place,
            though no method is 100% secure. Use of our Services constitutes
            understanding and acceptance of these risks.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Data Breaches:</strong> We will notify affected users and
            comply with applicable laws.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Location:</strong> Servers are based in the U.S., though data
            may be stored or processed in other countries.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Your Data Rights</h2>
        <p>
          If you live in a jurisdiction with privacy laws such as the EU GDPR or
          CCPA, you may have the right to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Know what data we collect</li>
          <li>Access and obtain a copy of your data</li>
          <li>Request corrections</li>
          <li>Request deletion</li>
          <li>Restrict processing</li>
          <li>Object to processing</li>
          <li>Request data portability</li>
          <li>Opt out of the sale or sharing of your data</li>
          <li>Exercise your rights without discrimination</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise these rights, contact{' '}
          <a href="mailto:connect@openteams.com">connect@openteams.com</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Children’s Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our Services are not directed at children under 16. We do not
          knowingly collect data from minors. If a child has submitted data,
          please contact us so we can delete it.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookie Notice</h2>
        <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Understand how You use Our Services</li>
          <li>Improve user experience and personalization</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>Third-Party Retargeting Cookies (RB2B):</strong> When you
          visit or log in to our website, cookies and similar technologies may
          be used by our data partners to associate activity with your personal
          information, including your email address. This may result in
          email-based or personalized advertising.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Opt out:{' '}
            <a href="https://app.retention.com/optout">https://app.retention.com/optout</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            GDPR opt out (if applicable):{' '}
            <a href="https://www.rb2b.com/rb2b-gdpr-opt-out">https://www.rb2b.com/rb2b-gdpr-opt-out</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          For questions, contact{' '}
          <a href="mailto:connect@openteams.com">connect@openteams.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose { max-width: 760px; }
  .prose h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; }
  .prose ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .prose li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; list-style: disc; }
</style>
